; S:CMenu/Config - menu definition for CMenu
;
; One item per line:  Menu name|path-to-script-or-executable
; Max 10 items (keys 1-9 and 0 launch them directly).
;
; DEFAULT n    - 1-based index of the preselected item (default 1)
; TIMEOUT secs - start the DEFAULT item after secs seconds unless a
;                key is pressed; 0 or absent = wait forever
; STYLE LIGHT|DARK|ANSI
;              - LIGHT = grey bg/black text, DARK = black bg/white
;                text, ANSI = DARK plus full-colour art
;                (default DARK)
; HEADERS [ON|OFF] dir
;              - directory with ANSI art headers; one is picked at
;                random each run and drawn above the menu. OFF keeps
;                the dir configured but hides the header
; BACKGROUND [ON|OFF] path
;              - full-screen background art (file, or directory to
;                rotate) instead of a header; the menu is laid out
;                inside the art's free interior

Workbench|S:Startup-Sequence-Normal
Shell|C:NewShell
DEFAULT 1
TIMEOUT 10
STYLE DARK
HEADERS ON S:CMenu/Headers
BACKGROUND OFF S:CMenu/Backgrounds
